@pawel, I think the idea here is to add an exception into that line of code.

@hemanth, you are right. If this problem happening post live-migrate, going into the ERROR state is correct, because the admin needs to clean up, and there is no sensible way to revert the operation. If this happens during the pre-live-migrate setup/checks, we probably should go back to ACTIVE, if we can do a full revert.

So I think incomplete is a valid state, while we narrow down the issue we are talking about here.
